**Missing Library**: `libAFL.a` - General AFL++ runtime (not present in OSS-Fuzz containers)\n\n## CORRECT LINKER FLAGS\nThe correct linker flags should be:\n```bash\n-L/src/aflplusplus -lAFLDriver\n```\nNOT:\n```bash\n-L/src/aflplusplus -lAFLDriver -lAFL  # Wrong: -lAFL doesn't exist\n```\n\n## POTENTIAL FIX STRATEGIES\n\n### STRATEGY A: Fix library linking in build.sh\nUpdate the build.sh to use only the available libraries:\n```bash\nexport LDFLAGS=\"${LDFLAGS:-} -L/src/aflplusplus -lAFLDriver\"\nexport BAZEL_EXTRA_BUILD_FLAGS=\"$BAZEL_EXTRA_BUILD_FLAGS --linkopt=-L/src/aflplusplus --linkopt=-lAFLDriver\"\n```\n\n### STRATEGY B: Check if libAFLDriver.a contains required symbols\nVerify that `libAFLDriver.a` contains the missing AFL symbols:\n```bash\nnm /src/aflplusplus/libAFLDriver.a | grep -E \"__afl_manual_init|__afl_fuzz_ptr|__afl_persistent_loop\"\n```\n\n### STRATEGY C: Investigate AFL++ compiler wrapper behavior\nThe AFL++ compiler wrappers (`afl-clang-fast`, `afl-clang-fast++`) should automatically add the correct linker flags. The issue might be that Bazel is bypassing the wrapper's linker phase.\n\n### STRATEGY D: Use static library path directly\nInstead of `-lAFLDriver`, use the full path:\n```bash\n-L/src/aflplusplus /src/aflplusplus/libAFLDriver.a\n```\n\n## COMMON PITFALLS WITH AFL++ IN BAZEL\n1. **Library Naming**: AFL++ uses different library names in different distributions\n2. **Compiler Wrapper Bypass**: Bazel might call the linker directly, bypassing AFL++ wrapper flags\n3. **Static vs Dynamic**: AFL++ typically uses static libraries (.a files)\n4. **Symbol Visibility**: Some AFL++ symbols might be hidden or have different naming\n\n## DIAGNOSTIC STEPS\n1. Check library contents: `nm /src/aflplusplus/libAFLDriver.a | grep __afl`\n2. Verify linker command: Add `--subcommands` to Bazel to see exact linker invocation\n3. Test simple linking: Try linking a simple test program with AFL++ libraries outside Bazel\n\n## PRIORITY RECOMMENDATIONS\n1. *