  - TOOL_CALL: create_or_update_file({"file_path": "expert_knowledge.txt", "content": "# Expert Knowledge for AFL++ Linker Errors in OSS-Fuzz Bazel Builds\n\n## Root Cause Analysis\nThe build log shows multiple linker errors with undefined AFL symbols:\n- `__afl_manual_init`\n- `__afl_fuzz_ptr`\n- `__afl_persistent_loop`\n- `__afl_fuzz_len`\n- `__afl_area_ptr`\n- `__afl_map_size`\n\nThese symbols are referenced from `aflpp_driver.o` in `external/+non_module_dependencies+rules_fuzzing_oss_fuzz/oss_fuzz_engine.a` but are not found during linking.\n\n## Historical Context\nPrevious attempts (643 attempts in history) reveal:\n1. `libAFLDriver.a` in OSS-Fuzz container is only a 28KB stub library with undefined references (U) to AFL symbols\n2. The actual AFL++ runtime that defines these symbols is missing from the OSS-Fuzz container\n3. This is a systemic OSS-Fuzz infrastructure issue, not a project-specific configuration problem\n\n## Key Observations from Build Log\n1. **Build Environment**: Using AFL++ with address sanitizer on x86_64 architecture\n2. **Bazel Configuration**: Build uses `--@rules_fuzzing//fuzzing:cc_engine=@rules_fuzzing_oss_fuzz//:oss_fuzz_engine`\n3. **Compiler Setup**: CC=/src/aflplusplus/afl-clang-fast, CXX=/src/aflplusplus/afl-clang-fast++\n4. **Linker**: Using clang-22 with ld.lld linker\n5. **Build Progress**: Compilation succeeds, linking fails at final stage\n\n## Common Fix Patterns for AFL Linking Issues\n\n### Pattern 1: Missing AFL Runtime Library\n**Symptoms**: Undefined AFL symbols during linking\n**Root Cause**: AFL runtime library not linked or missing\n**Solutions**:\n1. Add `-lAFLDriver` or `-lAFL` to linker flags\n2. Ensure AFL runtime library is installed in container\n3. Check if AFL++ was built with proper runtime support\n\n### Pattern 2: Bazel Configuration Issues\n**Symptoms**: Bazel not passing AFL libraries to linker\n**Root Cause**: Bazel build rules not configured for AFL linking\n**Solutions**:\n1. Add `linkopts = [\"-lAFLDriver\"]` to cc_fuzz_test rules\n2. Modify Bazel toolchain to include AFL libraries\n3. Use `--linkopt=-lAFLDriver` in Bazel command line\n\n### Pattern 3: OSS-Fuzz Container Issues\n**Symptoms**: AFL libraries exist but are stub/placeholder\n**Root Cause**: OSS-Fuzz base image has incomplete AFL installation\n**Solutions**:\n1. Install complete AFL++ package in Dockerfile\n2. Build AFL++ from source in container\n3. Use different fuzzing engine (libFuzzer instead of AFL)\n\n## Recommended Investigation Steps\n\n1. **Check AFL Installation**:\n   ```bash\n   find /src -name \"*AFL*\" -type f\n   ls -la /src/aflplusplus/\n   nm /src/aflplusplus/afl-clang-fast | grep __afl\n   ```\n\n2. **Verify Library Contents**:\n   ```bash\n   find /src -name \"libAFL*.a\" -o -name \"libAFL*.so\"\n   nm /src/aflplusplus/libAFLDriver.a 2>/dev/null | head -20\n   ```\n\n3. **Test Simple AFL Linking**:\n   ```bash\n   echo \"int main() { return 0; }\" > test.c\n   /src/aflplusplus/afl-clang-fast test.c -o test -lAFLDriver\n   ```\n\n4. **Check Bazel Link Command**:\n   Examine the actual link command from Bazel logs to see what libraries are being linked.\n\n## Potential Fix Strategies\n\n### Strategy A: Modify Bazel Build Configuration\n- Add AFL linker flags to project's BUILD files\n- Modify `rules_fuzzing` configuration to include AFL libraries\n- Use `--linkopt` Bazel flags\n\n### Strategy B: Fix OSS-Fuzz Container\n- Update Dockerfile to install complete AFL++ runtime\n- Build AFL++ from source with proper runtime support\n- Use pre-built AFL++ binaries with runtime included\n\n### Strategy C: Switch Fuzzing Engine\n- Change from AFL to libFuzzer (often more compatible with OSS-Fuzz)\n- Modify project configuration to use different engine\n\n## Critical Insight\nThe error occurs at linking stage, indicating compilation succeeds but the final executable cannot be created due to missing AFL runtime symbols. This suggests the AFL compiler wrappers (afl-clang-fast) are being used correctly, but the runtime library they depend on is not available or not being linked."})
