  - TOOL_CALL: create_or_update_file({"file_path": "expert_knowledge_v2.txt", "content": "# Expert Knowledge Update: AFL++ Linker Errors in OSS-Fuzz Bazel Builds - Part 2\n\n## Current Status Analysis\nPrevious fix attempt (Strategy C) made partial progress:\n- **Success**: Changed compiler from `afl-clang-fast` to regular `clang` (`CC=/usr/local/bin/clang`, `CXX=/usr/local/bin/clang++`)\n- **Failure**: Linking still fails with same AFL undefined symbols\n- **Root Cause**: Bazel configuration still uses AFL engine (`--@rules_fuzzing//fuzzing:cc_engine=@rules_fuzzing_oss_fuzz//:oss_fuzz_engine`)\n\n## Key Insight from Attempt 643\n**Changing compiler environment variables is insufficient**. The Bazel build configuration needs to be modified to use a different engine (e.g., libFuzzer engine instead of the OSS-Fuzz AFL engine).\n\n## The Core Problem\nThe `oss_fuzz_engine.a` archive contains `aflpp_driver.o` which references AFL runtime symbols (`__afl_manual_init`, `__afl_fuzz_ptr`, etc.). Even with regular clang compiler, this archive is still being linked, causing the same undefined symbol errors.\n\n## Historical Context Summary\n1. **Attempt 0-642**: Various attempts to fix AFL linking, all failed\n2. **Attempt 4**: Discovered `libAFLDriver.a` is only a 28KB stub library with undefined references\n3. **Attempt 642**: Identified as systemic OSS-Fuzz infrastructure issue (missing AFL runtime)\n4. **Attempt 643**: Partial success - changed compiler but not Bazel engine configuration\n\n## Recommended Next Steps\n\n### Strategy C.1: Modify Bazel Configuration to Use libFuzzer Engine\nInstead of just changing compiler environment variables, modify the Bazel build command to use libFuzzer engine:\n\n**Current Bazel command (from logs)**:\n```\n--@rules_fuzzing//fuzzing:cc_engine=@rules_fuzzing_oss_fuzz//:oss_fuzz_engine\n```\n\n**Should be changed to**:\n```\n--@rules_fuzzing//fuzzing:cc_engine=@rules_fuzzing//fuzzing/engines:libfuzzer\n```\n\n### Strategy C.2: Update build.sh to Modify Bazel Flags\nThe `bazel_build_fuzz_tests` function likely uses the `--@rules_fuzzing//fuzzing:cc_engine` flag. Need to override this when AFL is selected.\n\n### Strategy C.3: Check if OSS-Fuzz Environment Supports Engine Switching\nInvestigate if OSS-Fuzz build infrastructure allows engine switching via environment variables or configuration.\n\n## Investigation Needed\n\n1. **Examine Bazel Configuration Files**:\n   - Check `.bazelrc` in the project\n   - Look for `build:oss-fuzz` configuration\n   - Check `fuzzing/engines/BUILD` for engine definitions\n\n2. **Understand OSS-Fuzz Integration**:\n   - How does `rules_fuzzing` integrate with OSS-Fuzz?\n   - What does `@rules_fuzzing_oss_fuzz//:oss_fuzz_engine` actually provide?\n\n3. **Check Project Configuration**:\n   - Look at `project.yaml` - supports libfuzzer, afl, honggfuzz\n   - Check if engine can be specified in project configuration\n\n## Critical Observations from Build Log\n\n1. **Compiler Change Worked**: `CC=/usr/local/bin/clang`, `CXX=/usr/local/bin/clang++` (visible in link commands)\n2. **Engine Still AFL**: Still linking against `oss_fuzz_engine.a` with AFL symbols\n3. **Bazel Configuration Persistent**: Engine selection seems to be baked into Bazel configuration\n\n## Potential Solutions\n\n### Solution 1: Modify .bazelrc\nIf there's a `.bazelrc` file with `build:oss-fuzz` configuration, modify it to use libfuzzer engine instead of `oss_fuzz_engine`.\n\n### Solution 2: Override in build.sh\nAdd Bazel flags to override engine selection:\n```bash\nexport BAZEL_EXTRA_BUILD_FLAGS=\"--spawn_strategy=sandboxed --@rules_fuzzing//fuzzing:cc_engine=@rules_fuzzing//fuzzing/engines:libfuzzer\"\n```\n\n### Solution 3: Use Different Build Configuration\nIf OSS-Fuzz has different build configurations for different engines, switch to libfuzzer configuration.\n\n## Risk Assessment\n- **Low Risk**: Switching to libfuzzer should work since project.yaml lists libfuzzer as supported\n- **Medium Complexity**: Need to understand Bazel configuration system\n- **High Impact**: Could finally resolve the persistent AFL linking issue\n\n## Recommended Immediate Action\n1. Check for `.bazelrc` file in project\n2. Look at how `bazel_build_fuzz_tests` function works\n3. Modify build.sh to override engine selection when AFL is detected"})
