  - STATE_UPDATE: {'generated_prompt': 'You are a premier expert in software testing. Fix the build for: bazel-rules-fuzzing-test.\n\n--- 【LESSONS FROM PREVIOUS ATTEMPTS】 ---\n- [Attempt 642] Fresh build after complete environment reset shows identical AFL linking errors as all previous attempts. Historical analysis (attempt 4) revealed the root cause: libAFLDriver.a in OSS-Fuzz container is only a 28KB stub library with undefined references (U) to AFL symbols, not the actual AFL++ runtime. The actual AFL++ runtime that defines __afl_manual_init, __afl_fuzz_ptr, etc. is missing from the container. This is a systemic OSS-Fuzz infrastructure issue, not a project-specific configuration problem. Need to either: 1) Install complete AFL++ runtime in container, 2) Use different fuzzing engine, or 3) Modify build to link against proper AFL libraries.\n- [Attempt 643] Fix partially successful: compiler changed from afl-clang-fast to regular clang (CC=/usr/local/bin/clang, CXX=/usr/local/bin/clang++). However, linking still fails with same AFL undefined symbols because Bazel configuration still uses AFL engine (--@rules_fuzzing//fuzzing:cc_engine=@rules_fuzzing_oss_fuzz//:oss_fuzz_engine). The oss_fuzz_engine.a archive contains aflpp_driver.o which references AFL runtime symbols. Changing compiler environment variables is insufficient; need to modify Bazel configuration to use different engine (e.g., libFuzzer engine instead of OSS-Fuzz AFL engine).\n- [Attempt 1] Build failed with identical linker errors as original: undefined AFL symbols (__afl_manual_init, __afl_fuzz_ptr, etc.) in oss_fuzz_engine.a archive. The initial setup didn\'t address the core linking issue. Lesson: Need to investigate AFL runtime linking configuration in Bazel build system.\n\n\n--- Configuration Files (Dockerfile, build.sh, etc.) ---\n\n### Content from: Dockerfile ###\n# Copyright 2021 Google LLC\n#\n# Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the "License");\n# you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n# You may obtain a copy of the License at\n#\n#      http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n#\n# Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n# distributed under the License is distributed on an "AS IS" BASIS,\n# WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n# See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n# limitations under the License.\n#\n################################################################################\n\nFROM gcr.io/oss-fuzz-base/base-builder@sha256:c099d3d710d12d5d9a39498463ff10973977d1c7a85e9a0fbe00c7f0a0fa9fb8\n\nRUN apt-get update && \\\n    apt-get install -y python-is-python3\n\nRUN git clone https://github.com/bazelbuild/rules_fuzzing.git\nWORKDIR $SRC/rules_fuzzing/\nCOPY build.sh $SRC/\n\n### Content from: build.sh ###\n#!/bin/bash -eu\n#\n# Copyright 2021 Google LLC\n#\n# Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the "License");\n# you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n# You may obtain a copy of the License at\n#\n#      http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n#\n# Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n# distributed under the License is distributed on an "AS IS" BASIS,\n# WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n# See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n# limitations under the License.\n#\n################################################################################\n\n# Work around https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/issues/21592: \n# The `layering_check` feature does not work with `--spawn_strategy=standalone`,\n# which is the default for OSS-Fuzz builds.\nexport BAZEL_EXTRA_BUILD_FLAGS="--spawn_strategy=sandboxed"\n\nbazel_build_fuzz_tests\n\n### Content from: project.yaml ###\nhomepage: "https://github.com/bazelbuild/rules_fuzzing"\nmain_repo: "https://github.com/bazelbuild/rules_fuzzing"\nlanguage: c++\nprimary_contact: "test@example.com"\n\nfuzzing_engines:\n  - libfuzzer\n  - afl\n  - honggfuzz\n\nsanitizers:\n  - address\n  - undefined\n  - memory\n\n# This is a test project.\ndisabled: true\n\n\n--- Project File Tree (Shallow View) ---\n📁 bazel-rules-fuzzing-test\n├── 📄 BUILD\n├── 📄 CODEOWNERS\n├── 📄 LICENSE\n├── 📄 MODULE.bazel\n├── 📄 MODULE.bazel.lock\n├── 📄 README.md\n├── 📄 WORKSPACE\n├── 📄 WORKSPACE.bzlmod\n├── 📄 bazel-bin\n├── 📄 bazel-out\n├── 📄 bazel-rules_fuzzing\n├── 📄 bazel-testlogs\n├── 📁 docs\n├── 📁 examples\n├── 📁 fuzzing\n├── 📄 honggfuzz.BUILD\n└── 📄 update_docs.sh\n\n--- Recent Commit Changes ---\n--- Commit Context Information ---\nProject Name: bazel-rules-fuzzing-test\nError Report Time: 2025-12-30\nSelected Commit SHA: 1b9ddac66217c77f4eea0d3a8b765953ab5080b5\n------------------------------\n\ncommit 1b9ddac66217c77f4eea0d3a8b765953ab5080b5\nAuthor: Fabian Meumertzheim <fabian@meumertzhe.im>\nDate:   Sat Sep 28 20:46:56 2024 +0200\n\n    Add aliases for OSS-Fuzz engines (#258)\n    \n    This allows Bzlmod users to reference the engines without reaching into rules_fuzzing internals.\n---\n .bazelrc              |  4 ++--\n docs/guide.md         | 25 +++++++++++++++++--------\n fuzzing/engines/BUILD | 15 +++++++++++++++\n 3 files changed, 34 insertions(+), 10 deletions(-)\n\ndiff --git a/.bazelrc b/.bazelrc\nindex 876b6f5..bb94580 100644\n--- a/.bazelrc\n+++ b/.bazelrc\n@@ -84,8 +84,8 @@ build:asan-ubsan-replay --//fuzzing:cc_engine=//fuzzing/engines:replay\n build:asan-ubsan-replay --@rules_fuzzing//fuzzing:cc_engine_instrumentation=none\n build:asan-ubsan-replay --@rules_fuzzing//fuzzing:cc_engine_sanitizer=asan-ubsan\n \n-build:oss-fuzz --//fuzzing:cc_engine=@rules_fuzzing_oss_fuzz//:oss_fuzz_engine\n-build:oss-fuzz --//fuzzing:java_engine=@rules_fuzzing_oss_fuzz//:oss_fuzz_java_engine\n+build:oss-fuzz --//fuzzing:cc_engine=@rules_fuzzing//fuzzing/engines:oss_fuzz\n+build:oss-fuzz --//fuzzing:java_engine=@rules_fuzzing//fuzzing/engines:oss_fuzz_java\n build:oss-fuzz --@rules_fuzzing//fuzzing:cc_engine_instrumentation=oss-fuzz\n build:oss-fuzz --@rules_fuzzing//fuzzing:cc_engine_sanitizer=none\n \ndiff --git a/docs/guide.md b/docs/guide.md\nindex 28b5ba3..39fe022 100644\n--- a/docs/guide.md\n+++ b/docs/guide.md\n@@ -1,13 +1,22 @@\n+<!-- omit from toc -->\n # Bazel Rules User Guide\n \n+<!-- omit from toc -->\n ## Contents\n \n-* [Defining fuzz tests](#defining-fuzz-tests)\n-* [Integrating in your project](#integrating-in-your-project)\n-* [Advanced topics](#advanced-topics)\n-  * [Defining fuzzing engines](#defining-fuzzing-engines)\n-  * [Customizing fuzz tests](#customizing-fuzz-tests)\n-* [Rule reference](#rule-reference)\n+- [Defining fuzz tests](#defining-fuzz-tests)\n+  - [Defining fuzz tests](#defining-fuzz-tests-1)\n+  - [Building and running](#building-and-running)\n+  - [Specifying seed corpora](#specifying-seed-corpora)\n+  - [Specifying dictionaries](#specifying-dictionaries)\n+  - [The fuzz test launcher](#the-fuzz-test-launcher)\n+  - [Built-in fuzzing engines](#built-in-fuzzing-engines)\n+  - [Configuration flags](#configuration-flags)\n+- [Integrating in your project](#integrating-in-your-project)\n+  - [Configuring the .bazelrc file](#configuring-the-bazelrc-file)\n+- [Advanced topics](#advanced-topics)\n+  - [Defining fuzzing engines](#defining-fuzzing-engines)\n+- [Rule reference](#rule-reference)\n \n ## Defining fuzz tests\n \n@@ -121,11 +130,11 @@ Currently, the launcher offers the following options:\n \n * `@rules_fuzzing//fuzzing/engines:libfuzzer` provides libFuzzer support. Must be used with the `libfuzzer` engine instrumentation.\n \n-* `@rules_fuzzing//fuzzing/engines:honggfuzz` provides Honggfuzz support. Must be used with the `honggfuzz` engine instrumentation. Requires importing its dependencies using the `honggfuzz_dependencies()` WORKSPACE function.\n+* `@rules_fuzzing//fuzzing/engines:honggfuzz` provides Honggfuzz support. Must be used with the `honggfuzz` engine instrumentation. When using WORKSPACE, requires importing its dependencies using the `honggfuzz_dependencies()` WORKSPACE function.\n \n * `@rules_fuzzing//fuzzing/engines:replay` provides a simple engine that just executes a set of test files. It can be combined with a sanitizer and can be used for regression tests or replaying crashes.\n \n-* `@rules_fuzzing_oss_fuzz//:oss_fuzz_engine` provides a fuzzing engine that reflects the environment configuration of an [OSS-Fuzz build][bazel-oss-fuzz]. This engine is useful in the `build.sh` script of an OSS-Fuzz project. Requires importing its dependencies using the `oss_fuzz_dependencies()` WORKSPACE function.\n+* `@rules_fuzzing//fuzzing/engines:oss_fuzz` and `:oss_fuzz_java` provide fuzzing engines that reflect the environment configuration of an [OSS-Fuzz build][bazel-oss-fuzz]. These engines are useful in the `build.sh` script of an OSS-Fuzz project. When using WORKSPACE, this requires importing its dependencies using the `oss_fuzz_dependencies()` function.\n \n ### Configuration flags\n \ndiff --git a/fuzzing/engines/BUILD b/fuzzing/engines/BUILD\nindex 8f99fba..a8f122d 100644\n--- a/fuzzing/engines/BUILD\n+++ b/fuzzing/engines/BUILD\n@@ -80,3 +80,18 @@ java_library(\n         "@rules_fuzzing_jazzer_api//jar",\n     ],\n )\n+\n+# OSS-Fuzz specification.\n+#########################\n+\n+alias(\n+    name = "oss_fuzz",\n+    actual = "@rules_fuzzing_oss_fuzz//:oss_fuzz_engine",\n+    visibility = ["//visibility:public"],\n+)\n+\n+alias(\n+    name = "oss_fuzz_java",\n+    actual = "@rules_fuzzing_oss_fuzz//:oss_fuzz_java_engine",\n+    visibility = ["//visibility:public"],\n+)\n\n\n--- Fuzz Build Log (Last 500 lines) ---\n    Fetching https://github.com/...nu-install_only.tar.gz; 65.5 MiB (65.1%) 6s\n\n\x1b[1A\x1b[K\n\x1b[1A\x1b[K\n\x1b[1A\x1b[K\n\x1b[1A\x1b[K\n\x1b[1A\x1b[K\x1b[32mAnalyzing:\x1b[0m 6 targets (86 packages loaded, 1858 targets configured)\n    Fetching ...thon++python+python_3_12_x86_64-unk